	<TABLE><TR><TD><IMG SRC="graphics/button.gif" ALIGN="TOP"></TD><TD><FONT FACE=" Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" SIZE=+1 COLOR="#000000"><A NAME="Paw Overhauled?"><B>Paw Overhauled?</B></A></FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE=" Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" SIZE=+1 COLOR="#000000">1999-11-18</FONT></TD><TD></TD></TR></TABLE><TABLE><TR><TD><FONT FACE=" Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" SIZE=2 COLOR="#000000">Rumors on UseNet have it that Infected Paw will be getting the "Kithicor" treatment in an upcoming patch. Seems that on the test server they recently had a GM event similar to the "Halloween Massacre" that was held in Kithicor on all the servers. Afterwards, word has it, the dungeon was repopulated with level 30+ mobs. Brad McQuaid responded to a few posts in this thread, and his answers hint that this will be going to the live servers soon. Here is what he had to say...<BR><BR>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ariel" COLOR="#0000FF">
<B>Post:</B><BR>
Whee, go figure - more ass kissing of the power gaming elite by Verant.  When will it end (NEVER)?<BR><BR>
</FONT>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ariel" COLOR="#FF0000">
<B>Brad's Reply</B><BR>
It so happens that most of our players are getting near mid level, and that this zone is targetted to be mid level now.<BR><BR>
</FONT>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ariel" COLOR="#0000FF">
<B>Post:</B><BR>
BTW - PAW is one of the worst designed levels I've ever seen, even comparing it to old doom 2D ones.  Jezuz, the vertigo I got in that traveling the long one way tunnels - no depth of design at all.<BR><BR>
</FONT>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ariel" COLOR="#FF0000">
<B>Brad's Reply</B><BR>
Seriously, I think you must be thinking about another dungeon... or another game.<BR><BR>
</FONT>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ariel" COLOR="#0000FF">
<B>Post:</B><BR>
Hardly anyone hunts there anyway so I guess it needed SOMETHING to be changed about it.<BR><BR>
</FONT>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ariel" COLOR="#FF0000">
<B>Brad's Reply</B><BR>
Agreed -- lower level players rarely went to Paw, probably because of it's distance.  So, now that most of our players are approaching mid-level, we've changed the zone's population (and treasure) in hopes it will be more popular now.<BR><BR>
</FONT>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ariel" COLOR="#0000FF">
